<FIRST>r i PM-Italy-USRescue     04-14 0162</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Italy-US Rescue,0164</SECOND>
<HEAD>USS Roosevelt Rescues Sailors From Foundering Yachts</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NAPLES, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Helicopters from the carrier USS Theodore
Roosevelt rescued 15 Britons from four yachts foundering in rough
seas off Corsica.
   The U.S. 6th Fleet said the 35-foot Harlequin called for help
before dawn Thursday when its captain fell and broke a leg as the
sailboat struggled in 30-foot seas and 70-knot winds. Three other
sailboats sent distress calls by sunrise.
   Capt. Dayton W. Ritt, the Roosevelt's commanding officer, said
helicopters took off from the nuclear-powered carrier at first
light. Fourteen men and one woman were flown to safety during the
six-hour rescue.
   The skipper of the Harlequin, Malcolm Cross, was in stable
condition with a fractured right leg, doctors said. The other crew
members were in good condition aboard the carrier, which is to make
a routine port visit to Monaco today.
   The sailboats were part of a 16-boat flotilla en route from
Toulon, France, to Bonifacio, Corsica.
</TEXT>
