<FIRST>r w BC-HouseContraAidRollCall 3Takes   04-14 0499</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-House Contra Aid Roll Call, 3 Takes,470-up</SECOND>
<HEAD>With PM-Contra Aid Bjt</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Names of senators voting against the package and those not voting
are included in the PM-Contra Aid story.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is the 309-110 roll call Thursday by
which the House approved a $49.7 million package of non-military
aid to the Nicaraguan Contras.
   A ``yes'' vote is a vote to approve the aid.
   Voting yes were 152 Democrats and 157 Republicans.
   Voting no were 99 Democrats and 11 Republicans.
   X denotes those not voting.
   Present denotes those who voted they were ``present'' at the
time of the vote but did not vote ``yes'' or ``no'' on the issue.
   There are three vacancies in the 435-member House.
</TEXT>
