<FIRST>r a PM-WeatherpageWeather     04-14 0447</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0459</SECOND>
<HEAD>Showers In South, Snow In New England</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Rainshowers fell over parts of the south-central United States
today, and a cold front brought some snow to New England.
   Rain fell in Oklahoma, Arkansas, Louisiana and Texas early this
morning, with showers and thunderstorms in south Texas. Widely
scattered showers also were near the southern tip of Florida and
over the upper Mississippi Valley.
   The rest of the nation enjoyed dry weather.
   A freeze warning was in effect this morning for central
Maryland, northwestern Virginia and the eastern panhandle of West
Virginia.
   The nation's high Thursday was 98 degrees at Palm Springs, Calif.
   Today's forecast: a few thunderstorms over southern and central
Florida; rainshowers scattered over northern Maine, the upper Great
Lakes and northern Illinois; showers and occasional thunderstorms
from western portions of Kentucky and Tennessee across Mississippi,
Louisiana and the eastern two-thirds of Texas; and cloudy skies
from the Florida Panhandle across Alabama, the Tennessee Valley,
the remainder of Illinois and Missouri.
   High temperatures were to be in the 40s and 50s from New England
across New Jersey, across the northern Appalachians and the lower
Great Lakes, Michigan, northern Wisconsin, the upper Mississippi
Valley, the northern Plains and the upper Missouri Valley; in the
60s and 70s from southern Pennsylvania across northern Florida, the
Ohio and Tennessee valleys, the central Gulf of Mexico states, the
remainder of the Great Lakes, the lower two-thirds of the
Mississippi, the remainder of the Plains, the Rockies, the northern
Plateau, the Great Basin, the northern Pacific Coast and much of
the California coast; and in the 90s from southern Nevada across
southwest Arizona and southeast California. High temperatures over
much of the remainder of the nation were forecast in the 80s.
   Temperatures around the nation at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 26
degrees at Du Bois, Pa., to 78 degrees at Phoenix.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 51 fair; Boston 38 cloudy; Buffalo 31 fair;
Charleston, S.C., 46 fair; Cincinnati 37 fair; Cleveland 33 fair;
Detroit 33 partly cloudy; Miami 73 fair; New York 40 fair;
Philadelphia 38 fair; Pittsburgh 31 fair; Portland, Maine, 32
foggy; Washington 44 fair.
   _Central: Bismarck 39 cloudy; Chicago 45 fair; Dallas-Fort Worth
49 rain; Denver 40 fair; Des Moines 55 windy; Indianapolis 34 fair;
Kansas City 48 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul 44 fair; Nashville 45
fair; New Orleans 59 cloudy; St. Louis 52 cloudy.
   _West: Albuquerque 44 fair; Anchorage 37 partly cloudy; Las
Vegas 66 partly cloudy; Los Angeles 60 cloudy; Phoenix 75 fair;
Salt Lake City 48 partly cloudy; San Diego 63 cloudy; San Francisco
57 cloudy; Seattle 55 partly cloudy.
   _Canada: Montreal 34 partly cloudy; Toronto 30 fair.
</TEXT>
