<HEAD>Worshipers Protest Arrest of Moslem Cleric</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ASSIUT, Egypt (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police dispersed about 1,000 Moslem
worshipers protesting the arrest of a fundamentalist cleric outside
a mosque Friday, security sources said.
   Worshipers began anti-government chants after a prayer service
at the mosque, but the crowd quickly dispersed when 15 trucks
filled with riot police arrived, the sources said on condition of
anonymity.
   Some demonstrators threw stones at police, the sources said.
   Before the protest, police rounded up 200 Moslem extremists to
prevent them from participating, sources said.
