<FIRST>r i AM-NearCollision     04-14 0185</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Near Collision,0190</SECOND>
<HEAD>British Jet Misses Small Plane by 15 Feet</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FRANKFURT, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A British Airways Boeing 737
carrying 84 passengers came within 15 feet of colliding with a
small plane that veered into its path this week, aviation officials
said Friday.
   Three flight attendants were injured when the jet pilot suddenly
changed course to avoid the private plane, according to the federal
aviation safety office.
   The incident occurred Tuesday as the jet was preparing to land
in Duesseldorf on a regular flight from London. It was at an
altitude of 10,000 feet when the pilot saw a single-engine plane
enter his flight path, said Hans-Ulrich Ohl, a spokesman for the
flight safety office.
   The captain executed a maneuver and flew about 15 feet over the
small plane, Ohl said. The jet landed safely.
   Ohl said the small plane's presence in the area was ``completely
legal.'' The plane was not identified, he said.
   Ohl also said the jet pilot had done nothing wrong.
   He said his information came from the pilot of the British
Airways jet. The incident was being investigated.
</TEXT>
