<HEAD>Car Bomb Injures Two Civil Guards In Northern Spain</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PASAJES, Spain (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Suspected Basque separatists on Friday
detonated a bomb as a civil guard patrol car passed by, and two
guards were injured, police said.
   No group claimed responsibility for the blast in the town near
San Sebastian, about 200 miles northeast of Madrid near the French
border. Police blamed it on the separatist group ETA, an acronym
