<TEXT>
   The stock market suffered a broad setback Thursday, as the Dow
Jones average of 30 industrials dropped 23.65 points to 2,296.00.
   Bond prices fell, reflecting nervousness about inflation.
   The dollar finished lower against major foreign currencies in
hectic trading, buffeted by a hike in interest rates by a key
European bank.
   Palladium futures prices soared to an 8-year high; platinum and
gold futures rose while silver futures were mixed; petroleum
futures plunged; grains and soybeans were mixed; and livestock and
meat futures were mixed.
