<FIRST>r f PM-GAF-Sutton     04-14 0154</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-GAF-Sutton,0162</SECOND>
<HEAD>GAF Acquires Sutton Labs</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WAYNE, N.J. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   GAF Corp. has has acquired Sutton
Laboratories, a Chatham-based specialty chemicals manufacturer of
preservatives for the cosmetic and toiletries industry, officials
say.
   No financial details were made public in the Thursday
announcement.
   Sutton is GAF's first acquisition since it became a private
company in October, said Samuel J. Heyman, chairman and chief
executive officer for GAF.
   ``Sutton is a strategic acquistion that strengthens our
long-term major commitment to the cosmetic, toiletries and
healthcare industries,'' Heyman said in a written statement.
   GAF will operate Sutton as a free-standing subsidiary under its
current names. William Rosen, formerly executive vice president of
Sutton, has been named president and will have full responsibility
for Sutton's worldwide operations.
   Sutton was founded in 1955 and produces preservatives used for
shampoos, conditioners and other hair preparations, hand and body
creams and lotions, bubble baths, cleansers, makeup, mascaras and
sun-screen preparations.
</TEXT>
