<HEAD>GM Boosts Rebates on Some Cars</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   General Motors Corp. on Friday increased
incentives on some of its Chevrolet, Buick, Oldsmobile and Pontiac
cars even as the company pushed its new low-financing program.
   The automaker boosted or added cash rebates on a variety of cars
and light trucks and offered options of financing as low as 2.9
percent on some vehicles.
   On March 30, GM announced a new incentive program, in effect
until June 5, that essentially matched a program announced the day
before by Ford Motor Co. Both companies offered interest rates as
low as 2.9 percent for two-year loans.
   On April 3, Chrysler Corp. announced an incentive package
featuring interest-free financing for two-year loans.
